Two fixes for the status badge (basic connectivity) disagreeing with
the connectivity view (HTML), which kept saying "Connected":

- maybe_network(), fired by the UI on every window focus / online
  event, flips the store from Idle to InterruptingIdle. The badge
  renders that as "Updating…", the connectivity HTML as "Connected".
  The IMAP inbox_loop leaves the state within seconds (the interrupt
  wakes IDLE, it refetches and sets Idle again), but webimap_loop
  never drains interrupts in the happy path and its signalled_idle
  gate skipped set_idle() on empty polls — there to avoid emitting
  ConnectivityChanged on every 60s poll — so the badge stayed at
  "Updating…" until the next incoming message or error.
  Now ConnectivityStore::set() ignores unchanged values (no event
  or lock churn on repeats) and webimap_loop sets Idle
  unconditionally after every successful poll.

- After scheduler start, "Connecting…" only cleared when the first
  long-poll returned, which on an empty inbox means the full
  wait=60 seconds. The first poll — and the first one after an
  error backoff — now uses wait=0, so Connected (or recovery from
  an error) shows after a single round-trip.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
